# Secure Cross-Platform VPN Client

Flutter VPN app in `secure_vpn_client/`. Local plugin fork in `packages/v2ray_box/`.

## Read first

- `.cursor/AGENTS.md` — repo map and golden rules
- `.cursor/troubleshooting.md` — known Linux/subscription failures

## Non-negotiable security

- SOCKS inbound: `127.0.0.1` only, `auth: password`, per-session random credentials
- Never bind `0.0.0.0`, never use unauthenticated port 7890
- Wipe credentials and config files on disconnect
- Do not log credentials or write them to disk

## Desktop (Linux/Windows/macOS)

- Use **proxy mode** (`VpnMode.proxy`), not TUN
- `ConfigParser.injectSecureSocksInbound(..., proxyOnly: true)` strips VPN-only inbounds
- Core binaries are **not in git** — `scripts/fetch_cores.sh`

## Edit targets

- App logic: `secure_vpn_client/lib/`
- Native/Linux: `packages/v2ray_box/linux/`
- Do not edit files under `build/` or `.plugin_symlinks/` — they are ephemeral

## Commands (from `secure_vpn_client/`)

`flutter analyze` · `flutter test` · `flutter run -d linux` (full restart after native changes)
